From: nvidia-driver-injector <noreply@example.invalid>
Date: 2026-05-12
Subject: [PATCH 0006/0007] tb-egpu: DIAG telemetry surface (cluster P6)

Consolidates legacy 0018 (diag dump core), 0020 (LnkSta/AER extension),
0021 (Header Log + ASPM + LBMS extension), and the S2/DIAG-AER2 portion
of 0023 (root port AER + DPC) into one rich per-site state dump.

Legacy 0009 (Lever P-probe — 18 investigation-period markers in
uvm.c) is dropped entirely per the inventory recommendation; none of
the markers survived their original investigation.

Inventory items applied (per docs/patch-refactor-inventory.md "### P6"):

- Renames:
    tb_egpu_lever_m_diag_dump          -> tb_egpu_diag_dump
    (drop file-level "AORUS Lever M-recover [DIAG]" log prefix in
     favour of compact "tb_egpu [DIAG]")

  Functions ALREADY shipped under tb_egpu_* prefix in P2/P4 are kept
  as-is — the inventory's aspirational `tb_egpu_diag_dump_pdev` rename
  would have duplicated P4's `tb_egpu_close_diag_pdev`. Where the
  inventory's rename map and the as-shipped names diverge, the
  as-shipped name wins (no rename-shuffling for shuffle's sake).

- Three log line classes:
    [DIAG]      primary site dump — PMC_BOOT_0 + WPR2 + LnkSta + LnkCtl
                + AER status, always emitted.
    [DIAG-AER]  follow-up emitted ONLY when GPU AER status is non-zero
                — Header Log, UncMask, CapCtl, FirstErrPtr.
    [DIAG-AER2] root port AER + DPC + bridge masks (S2 expansion) —
                always emitted; cheap (one line).

- Six call sites:
    probe-end          end of nv_pci_probe                    (nv-pci.c)
    startdev-entry     entry of nv_start_device               (nv.c)
    pre-rmInit         immediately before rm_init_adapter     (nv.c)
    post-rmInit-FAIL   after rm_init_adapter failure          (nv.c)
    post-rmInit-OK     after rm_init_adapter success          (nv.c)
    mmio-enabled       inside nv_pci_mmio_enabled (re-introduced
                       from P2 — P2 had to drop this pending P6)

  Both close-path call sites (RM-side + UVM-side) are NOT P6 — they
  belong to P4 (close-path observability), which is always-on by design
  because close-path bug mitigation is observational.

- Module-internal helper re-use. Cluster P2 introduced four register-
  read helpers as file-static functions (tb_egpu_recover_read_wpr2,
  _walk_to_root_port, _read_dpc_state, _read_aer_full). P6 reuses all
  four. To enable cross-TU use without code duplication, P6 lifts the
  `static` qualifiers and adds declarations to nv-tb-egpu-recover.h.
  Symbols stay module-internal (no EXPORT_SYMBOL); only the linkage
  changes from file-static to translation-unit-external.

- Inter-commit history stripped. Legacy 0018's "After Commit 3 design
  is finalised, this diagnostic is removed or gated behind a kill
  switch" comment is gone — P6 IS that gate (Kconfig wiring in P7).

Cross-cluster touches:

- P2's nv-tb-egpu-recover.{c,h}: 4 helper functions lifted from
  file-static to module-internal linkage; declarations added to header.
- P2's nv_pci_mmio_enabled: the diag_dump call P2 had to drop pending
  P6 is re-introduced. P2's commit message explicitly forecast this.

Kconfig deferral:

- Per docs/patch-refactor-status.md "Kconfig wiring — DEFERRED to end
  of Phase 2 (mechanical once all 6 patches exist)", the
  CONFIG_NV_TB_EGPU_DIAG gating + sysfs reshuffle (last_aer_summary /
  last_pmc_boot_0 / last_detection_jiffies move to DIAG-only) land in
  P7 (build metadata + Kconfig wiring). P6 ships diag content unconditionally;
  P7 adds the gates and the default-OFF behaviour.
- Until P7, every probe / start-device cycle emits ~6 [DIAG] lines.
  Per memory feedback_observability_perturbs_bug, A/B verify on the
  live host before assuming behaviour transfers between refactor-rc1
  and pre-refactor production (where similar instrumentation has been
  live since 2026-05-06).

Files touched:
  kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-diag.c     new  (223 lines)
  kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-diag.h     new  (52 lines)
  kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-recover.c  -4 static qualifiers
  kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-recover.h  +37 (4 helper decls)
